So I have been going here since I moved back in May I tried all the other grocers around here too but seem to come back here much more often.
They have a Wells Fargo in here which is convenient for me.
They have a great alcohol selection that even includes some awesome craft brews.
They have managers specials that are fantastic like 6 pieces of mixed fruit for just a buck!!
I picked up some ginormous cups here for a buck each that are actually made in the USA!!
On Halloween they had a little set up for the kids to eat cookies and drink cider.
They had cake decorating too my girl loved it!!
Speaking of kids they also have day care up in here!
I would so take advantage of this option if I had a toddler.
I like the neighborhood feel of this Bashas and supporting local helps me sleep at night.
There is one down side to things but its never really bothered me.
There are not enough cashiers at times and it could be a problem if you were in a hurry all the time.

Well stocked and always nice people there.
There is a wells Fargo branch in the store too.
We had the pizza and @ 5.99 or 6.99 it was rather tasty.

I go here 3 or 4 times a week to get my all natural healthy foods.
The staff always remembers me and treats me so well.
The biggest issue at grocery stores is when there is a line of people and the staff doesnt open another lane, drives me nuts!!!
At this store, you will never see more than 3 people in line.
Their prices are great and the quality of produce is always on point.
Go Bashas

