After reading a stat about how much more money stays in the state when you shop local I made it my mission to keep my money in Arizona.
Bashas had to be my choice for groceries.
They are super friendly and always have what I need.
One of my favorites is they always thank you for shopping there.
My only little complaint is it can take awhile to check out, but it's worth it to me.
Also they did get rid of the kid care if that means anything to anyone.

