Good beer selection (well - at least different than your average supermarket).
Meat counter has tasty steaks if you are willing to pay the price (which isn't too bad when you want a good, well-marbled  porterhouse).
Frozen veggie section includes hard-to-find items like Haricots Vert.
Always a bonus!
Checkers are friendly and well-trained.
They know how to bag correctly.
The store is a bit older, so not a lot of the fancy aisles/floors/lighting.
In fact, the lighting is done with about a zillion fluorescent bulbs - so it can be a bit bright at night!

